# Cross-platform line-ending and binary policy.
# Rationale: Windows + core.autocrlf=true causes disk bytes to differ
# from tree bytes for text files, breaking raw-sha256 byte-identity
# checks used in Lane B/A/C audit rules. This file pins CSV and TXT
# artifacts to LF-on-disk so sha256sum of working-tree matches the
# tree blob, and marks generated binary outputs explicitly so git
# never attempts text normalization on them.
#
# Scope (C-as-drafted): CSV/TXT only. Source code (.py), notes (.md),
# and other text types intentionally left under the existing autocrlf
# default; expanding to those is a separate decision (C-extended)
# tracked as future work.

# Force LF on disk for analysis artifacts and audit text outputs
*.csv text eol=lf
*.txt text eol=lf

# Mark generated binaries explicitly so git never tries to normalize them
*.png binary
*.pdf binary
*.docx binary
*.pptx binary
*.xlsx binary
